1
00:00:52,024 --> 00:00:54,160
No more wine for me.

2
00:00:56,944 --> 00:01:00,024
Neither the murky red.

3
00:01:01,008 --> 00:01:05,008
Nor the bright one.

4
00:01:06,718 --> 00:01:09,164
I’m thirsty.

5
00:01:09,606 --> 00:01:11,606
Thirsty for my own blood.

6
00:01:20,944 --> 00:01:22,944
Man: Are we getting there?

7
00:01:23,026 --> 00:01:24,618
Woman: Yeah.

8
00:01:27,944 --> 00:01:33,464
Man: Do you see him? He's waving at you.

9
00:02:54,704 --> 00:02:56,788
Man: got all the bags?

10
00:02:57,944 --> 00:02:59,348
Woman: Ah! Sorry...

11
00:03:01,744 --> 00:03:04,685
...yeah, they’re all here.

12
00:03:11,330 --> 00:03:13,580
Man: Bismillah! ("move forward!")

13
00:03:39,943 --> 00:03:42,184
Man: What's he saying?

14
00:03:47,720 --> 00:03:50,741
Woman: Asks if we are together...

15
00:03:50,917 --> 00:03:53,565
Man: Say it's my wife.

16
00:04:17,105 --> 00:04:21,434
Man: When did you stored these in the luggage?

17
00:04:56,205 --> 00:04:58,298
Man: So, where is he?

18
00:04:58,657 --> 00:05:02,690
Woman: Maybe he’s outside waiting, we’re late. Want me to go look?

19
00:05:02,690 --> 00:05:04,366
Man: No, you stay right here.

20
00:05:04,366 --> 00:05:05,336
I check.

21
00:05:36,344 --> 00:05:39,263
Man: No praying room around...

22
00:05:47,738 --> 00:05:49,781
Man: Hello?

23
00:05:49,874 --> 00:05:51,256
Babak?

24
00:05:51,692 --> 00:05:53,545
Can you hear me?

25
00:05:53,795 --> 00:05:54,809
Hello?

26
00:05:55,515 --> 00:05:56,507
Hello?

27
00:05:57,252 --> 00:05:58,458
For God’s sake!

28
00:05:58,458 --> 00:06:00,458
Woman: What happened? Did it cut off?

29
00:06:00,458 --> 00:06:01,781
Call him again.

30
00:06:06,493 --> 00:06:08,788
Man: I don’t know where this boy is...

31
00:06:11,464 --> 00:06:16,583
Woman: Well, maybe he forgot we’re arriving tonight...

32
00:06:16,583 --> 00:06:22,544
Man: How do you mean, forgot? We’ve been planning this for 3 months now.

33
00:06:26,661 --> 00:06:27,930
Man: Hello?

34
00:06:29,369 --> 00:06:30,369
Hi Farideh.

35
00:06:31,576 --> 00:06:33,018
We are well.

36
00:06:33,764 --> 00:06:36,944
We’re still at the airport.

37
00:06:37,945 --> 00:06:39,945
No worries.

38
00:06:40,681 --> 00:06:41,784
Ok.

39
00:06:41,975 --> 00:06:43,975
I’ll call once we get home.

40
00:06:44,417 --> 00:06:45,240
Bye.

41
00:06:46,447 --> 00:06:52,241
Woman: I have his address. Let’s just get a taxi.

42
00:06:52,241 --> 00:06:54,090
Man: What if he’s not home?

43
00:06:54,090 --> 00:06:56,090
Woman: Let’s just go to his home. We find a way.

44
00:06:56,090 --> 00:06:58,090
Man: Wait in the street?

45
00:06:58,269 --> 00:07:03,109
Man: I’m not wandering around a city where we don’t know anyone or the language!

46
00:07:03,109 --> 00:07:05,663
Woman: We can’t stay here waiting till nightfall.

47
00:07:05,663 --> 00:07:10,029
Man: We’ll wait till night if we have to. He said he’d come. He has to come.

48
00:07:20,634 --> 00:07:23,924
[music]

49
00:08:14,464 --> 00:08:17,408
Man: Wait, Pari!

50
00:08:20,284 --> 00:08:22,224
Pari!

51
00:08:36,223 --> 00:08:39,223
Pari: Babak?

52
00:09:36,023 --> 00:09:39,722
Man: What are they saying?
Pari: They’re speaking Greek.

53
00:09:39,722 --> 00:09:41,722
Man: For God’s sake!

54
00:10:38,646 --> 00:10:42,304
Man: Where have they brought us, a barn?

55
00:10:42,304 --> 00:10:44,304
Don’t go in!

56
00:11:05,204 --> 00:11:08,084
Pari: This is Babak’s handwriting!

57
00:11:32,424 --> 00:11:34,624
Man: What?

58
00:11:37,176 --> 00:11:40,787
Pari: That Babak left here three months ago.

59
00:11:40,787 --> 00:11:42,787
Man: What?

60
00:11:53,704 --> 00:11:57,269
Man: What do they want?

61
00:11:57,269 --> 00:11:59,269
Pari: He owes them money.

62
00:12:11,450 --> 00:12:14,450
Man: Apologize to them.

63
00:13:05,763 --> 00:13:09,033
Official: When was the last time you saw your son?

64
00:13:09,691 --> 00:13:11,112
Man: Two years ago.

65
00:13:13,604 --> 00:13:18,120
Official: Has he ever mentioned any trouble with his university?

66
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:22,681
Man: No, Babak’s an excellent student. He’s here on a scholarship...

67
00:13:25,418 --> 00:13:27,361
...at their best university.

68
00:13:27,361 --> 00:13:29,361
University of Athens - Polytechnic.

69
00:13:29,544 --> 00:13:31,463
Official: Yes, we’re aware. His name is on the embassy’s list,

70
00:13:31,463 --> 00:13:33,951
but there seems to be a problem.

71
00:13:33,128 --> 00:13:34,011
Man: What kind of problem?

72
00:13:34,011 --> 00:13:38,395
Official: His scholarship has been revoked. It’s been over a year.

73
00:13:38,632 --> 00:13:42,592
Man: Are you sure? He never told us anything.

74
00:13:44,161 --> 00:13:47,046
Official: How come you haven’t seen each other in all this time?

75
00:13:47,046 --> 00:13:51,618
Man: Babak’s been very busy. He didn’t have time to come back to Iran,

76
00:13:51,618 --> 00:13:54,187
and we’re not the kind of family that travels abroad.

77
00:13:54,187 --> 00:13:58,483
Official: If you don’t travel abroad, why send your son here?

78
00:13:58,661 --> 00:14:02,142
Is anyone looking out for him?

79
00:14:02,819 --> 00:14:06,000
Official: Hajji, I understand.

80
00:14:07,298 --> 00:14:09,298
You’re a respectable family.

81
00:14:09,298 --> 00:14:12,000
But we’ve seen this situation many times here.

82
00:14:12,656 --> 00:14:16,590
Sadly, many of our youth lose their way

83
00:14:16,730 --> 00:14:18,321
because of their freedoms.

84
00:14:18,321 --> 00:14:20,734
so-called freedoms.

85
00:14:21,189 --> 00:14:26,104
Official: Iranian students often drop out and don’t tell their parents,

86
00:14:26,104 --> 00:14:29,799
just so they can keep receiving the scholarship money.

87
00:14:29,799 --> 00:14:31,821
Official: Do you understand what I mean?

88
00:14:31,821 --> 00:14:33,821
Pari: Babak would never do something like that.

89
00:14:36,944 --> 00:14:38,769
Man: Sir, what can we do in this foreign city?

90
00:14:39,975 --> 00:14:40,759
We don’t know anyo...

91
00:14:40,759 --> 00:14:42,033
Official: Mr. Bagheri,

92
00:14:42,033 --> 00:14:44,033
get the university’s address for Hajj Agha.

93
00:14:44,622 --> 00:14:46,622
Bagheri: Right away.

94
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:48,288
Official: At your service.

95
00:14:52,944 --> 00:14:54,160
No more wine for me.

96
00:14:56,184 --> 00:14:59,120
Neither the murky red.

97
00:14:59,487 --> 00:15:01,487
Nor the bright one.

98
00:15:05,504 --> 00:15:07,459
I’m thirsty.

99
00:15:07,459 --> 00:15:10,451
Thirsty for my own blood,

100
00:15:10,451 --> 00:15:12,451
spilled in the square.

101
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:01,359
Man: Why shaking head like that?

102
00:15:01,359 --> 00:15:03,635
Pari: He didn’t enroll this year.

103
00:15:05,196 --> 00:15:08,182
Man: Let’s go.

104
00:15:08,771 --> 00:15:10,108
I told you, let’s go.

105
